# Astro Pages & Components

## Page skeleton

```astro
---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
export const prerender = false; // or true for static marketing pages

const locale = 'da';
---

<Base locale={locale} title="Page Title | Akademisk Boldklub">
  <!-- content -->
</Base>
```

## Prerender

- `prerender = true` — static content only (e.g. `om/historik`, `om/stadion`)
- `prerender = false` — Strapi/SI data, auth, API-backed pages (default for most routes)

## React islands

Use React only for client interactivity. Import from `@/components/islands/` and hydrate explicitly:

```astro
import MobileMenu from '@/components/islands/MobileMenu';
<MobileMenu client:load nav={nav} locale={locale} enPrefix={enPrefix} />
```

Prefer `.astro` components for everything else (Navbar, widgets, cards).

## Frontmatter strings

Apostrophes in Danish/English copy break single-quoted strings. Use double quotes or escape:

```ts
// BAD — breaks esbuild
heading: 'AB's farver'

// GOOD
heading: "AB's farver"
heading: 'AB\'s farver'
```

## Resilient data fetching

Wrap CMS/API calls in try/catch; pages must render when Strapi/SI is down:

```ts
let data: Article[] = [];
try {
  data = await fetchCollectionType('articles', { locale });
} catch { /* CMS unavailable */ }
```

## Imports

- Use `@/` path alias (`@/layouts/Base.astro`, `@/lib/strapi/client`)
- TS/TSX island imports omit extension; `.astro` imports include `.astro`
